deterministic dictionary expansion function

Yes, that is one of the best places to test.

The clean idea is:

input term
→ existing definition
→ expansion rules
→ candidate related terms
→ stable ordered output

If deterministic, then:

same input + same db
→ same expansion

That is very testable.

pseudocode

function expandDictionary(term):
    base = lookup(term)

    if base missing:
        return []

    candidates = []

    candidates += synonyms(base)
    candidates += opposites(base)
    candidates += relatedByGematria(base)
    candidates += relatedByMeme(base)
    candidates += relatedByLineage(base)

    candidates = normalize(candidates)
    candidates = dedupe(candidates)
    candidates = sortStable(candidates)

    return candidates

More beast-aligned:

lookup
→ collect
→ normalize
→ dedupe
→ stable sort
→ output

deterministic rules

To keep it stable:

1. no randomness
2. fixed source order
3. fixed normalization rules
4. fixed sort order
5. same db snapshot during test

Example source order:

synonym
opposite
gematria
meme
lineage

So even if multiple sources return the same word, you always know why and where it came from first.

